{
  "texts": [
    "Meanwhile, classifying against Class 7, a total of 33 samples in that class are correctly discriminated, when 4 samples are misplaced cross-boundary among the adjacent classes.",
    "On the other end of the spectrum, the same in Class 8 classified a sample size of just 46 by the model, considering further at the fact that it is grossly misclassifying many into Class 14.",
    "These variations show one of the major challenges associated with dealing with medical-related datasets characterized by high similarities-that the proposed model fails at successfully classifying some of the prominent features which are comparable visibly.",
    "For segmentation tasks, good performance was obtained using U-Net on behalf of the majority of the classes, reaching a Dice Coefficient score of 0.96 for most classes.",
    "However, this score reduces quite a bit for the particular classes whose lesions either look very irregular or subtly differing in texture."
  ]
}